Hmm...got begged at in PoK yesterday, but still had my RP on.<br>
<br>
N00B_01 tells you, &quot;Hello&quot;<br>
<br>
You tell N00B_01, &quot;Yes?&quot;<br>
<br>
N00B_01 tells you, &quot;Do you have anything for a poor mage that only has the shirt on his back?&quot;<br>
<br>
You tell N00B_01, &quot;no&quot;<br>
<br>
(I'm pretty sure the short answer of no is not expected since most people will say something to qualify the no.  No works, and it gives them nothing to argue about.)<br>
<br>
The funny thing was the baited response he sent next.<br>
<br>
N00B_01 tells you, &quot;Thank you for your kindness as it reflects your true personality.&quot;  (or something to that effect)<br>
<br>
I thought it was funny.  I didn't say reply to him, but was going to ask, &quot;Is that EQ speak for Jesus loves you?&quot;  <br>
<br>
This guy must have been observing the begging techniques of the homeless, since they do some sort of similar parting guilt-trip line when you turn them down for a dollar on the street.  <br>
<br>
Bottom line is, say no and the less you say, the better.<br>
